    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="785"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3393/8–3147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-04T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 4, 1947—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1104. Believe Embassy in consultation with Tsingtao and Navy is in best position
                    to handle situation (Tsingtao’s 97, Aug 31, sent Nanking repeated Dept as 70).
                    Suggest (1) Navy exert utmost care in avoiding further armed clashes with
                    Communists (2) any trip by Service to Chefoo or elsewhere deep in Communist
                    territory (Sent Nanking as 1104 repeated Tsingtao as 66) be delayed for time
                    being pending outcome of negotiations between Navy and Communists now understood
                    to be under way.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
